T1  - Simple Economics of the Price-Setting Newsvendor Problem
AU  - Salinger, Michael
AU  - Ampudia, Miguel
Y1  - 2011/08/04
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/11/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.1110.1388
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.1110.1388
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1996
EP  - 1998
VL  - 57
IS  - 11
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The Lerner relationship linking the profit-maximizing price to marginal cost and the elasticity of demand generalizes to the price-setting newsvendor, and the result resolves the puzzle over the different effects of additive and multiplicative uncertainty on the solution. Multiplicative uncertainty increases the optimal price because it increases the marginal cost of a unit sold and does not affect the markup factor. Additive uncertainty has no effect on the marginal cost of a unit sold and lowers the markup factor because it increases the elasticity of the average quantity sold with respect to price. This paper was accepted by Martin Lariviere, operations management.
